  "body": "Start with a buggy contract and show how to debug it.  Contrive the contract so that \"debugging\" entails working through several iterations, with each iteration demonstrating a different debugging feature.  Perhaps:\r\n\r\n- Start with a contract that has already been deployed to a testnet.\r\n- Write the faulting function so that it's doing some naughty operation which would exhibit a failure without a reason on another network, but which has a clear failure reason in Hardhat Network.\r\n- Write the faulting function so that there is a series of similar operations, such that it's not clear which one of them is at fault, and guide the user to insert console.log statements to determine which statement is at fault.\r\n- etc",
